# ARTS Configuration Files

## Configuration File Structure
ARTS configuration files use INI format with `[ARTS]` section header.

## Essential Configuration Options

### Threading Configuration
```ini
worker_threads=16   # Worker threads per node
```

### GPU Support (Future)
```ini
scheduler=3             # GPU scheduler type
gpu=8                   # Number of GPUs
gpu_route_table_size=12 # GPU route table size
```

### Network Configuration
```ini
sender_threads=1   # Outgoing network threads
receiver_threads=1 # Incoming network threads
port_count=1       # Network ports per node
```

### Launcher Configuration
```ini
launcher=ssh          # Launch method (local, ssh, slurm, lsf)
master_node=localhost # Master node for SSH launcher
node_count=1          # Number of nodes
nodes=localhost       # Which nodes to run on
```

### Performance Monitoring
```ini
counter_folder=./counters     # Performance counter directory
counter_capture_interval=100  # Counter capture interval
```

### Memory and Performance
```ini
worker_init_deque_size=2048 # Initial deque size
route_table_size=16        # Routing table size
pin=1                      # Hardware pinning
```

## Example Configuration
See examples in [tests/examples/arts.cfg](mdc:tests/examples/arts.cfg):
```ini
[ARTS]
worker_threads=16
sender_threads=0
receiver_threads=0
port_count=1
launcher=local
master_node=localhost
node_count=1
nodes=localhost
default_ports=34739
counter_folder=./counters
```

## Configuration Locations
- Test directories: `test/*/arts.cfg`
- Example directories: `examples/*/arts.cfg`
- Each executable needs its own configuration file
